public ref class IisTraceListener sealed : System::Diagnostics::TraceListener

Docs.summary: Provides a listener that routes all tracing and debugging output to the IIS 7.0 infrastructure.

remarks.format:
## Remarks The <xref:System.Web.IisTraceListener> class connects the tracing mechanism of [!INCLUDE[vstecasp](~/includes/vstecasp-md.md)] to [!INCLUDE[iisver](~/includes/iisver-md.md)]. This listener class enables developers who create [!INCLUDE[vstecasp](~/includes/vstecasp-md.md)] applications and who implement the <xref:System.Web.IHttpModule> and <xref:System.Web.IHttpHandler> interfaces to raise page-level, module-level, or handler-level events to the [!INCLUDE[iisver](~/includes/iisver-md.md)] infrastructure when tracing is enabled.
> [!NOTE] > This listener class does not route [!INCLUDE[iisver](~/includes/iisver-md.md)] events to ASP.NET classes. This includes the <xref:System.Web.UI.Page> class and classes that implement the <xref:System.Web.IHttpModule> or <xref:System.Web.IHttpHandler> interface.
<xref:System.Web.IisTraceListener> is introduced in the [!INCLUDE[net_v35_long](~/includes/net-v35-long-md.md)]. For more information, see [Versions and Dependencies](~/docs/framework/migration-guide/versions-and-dependencies.md).
